			<parts.title>Argument in favour of aauthenticity of Naer het Leven drawings. The exotic types could be seen in Antwerp see e.g. Dürer's drawing of 1521 (Berlin) of Irish soldiers (repr. Waetzoldt, Dürer, fig. 234); Winkler, N° ? [sic]</parts.title>
			<parts.title>Dürer, Prayerbook (Strauss, p. 50=f. 25v: Bison) by Dürer in Munich part of Prayerbook, Strauss, p. 310=f. 155v [...] If the Prayerbook was owned by Granvelle, Bruegel might have seen it.</parts.title>
			<parts.title>Naer het Leven. Costumes. Procession to Calvary. My second edition pl. 72, Man left back, cf. Münz, pl. 89, N° 92, Man on right sadly the same dress, pl. 65 (old) Man with feather on head, bottom right, Münz, pl. 101. Generally Procession to Calvary & Sermon of Baptist most important for comparison of costumes.</parts.title>
